	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Famicom too, very nice looking. Though I'm not a huge fan of CHR-RAM, though it really depends on the project if I'd prefer RAM or ROM. Mainly I don't like CHR-RAM as you have no options for banking, and there is no DMA to VRAM like on SNES. 
<br />
<br />If you want something nice looking and designed for EPROM or Flash ROMs you should get a reproduction board from <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrousb.com">http://www.retrousb.com</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />If you have to use a real game please make sure it sucks and is common. You wouldn't want to destroy a decent or rare game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
