	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">electro wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">*Been wondering what other carts are like SMB?</div>
<br />Just use <a href="http://www.parodius.com/~veilleux/boardtable.txt" class="postlink">this document</a> for your board-checking needs. SMB uses an NROM board, as you can see in the list. You can search for other NROM games in there.
<br />
<br />The thing with NROM though is that there are 2 version, NROM-128 and NROM-256, one can hold 16KB of PRG ROM while the other holds 32KB. SMB uses 32KB, so it wouldn't be compatible with a NROM-128 board without modifications. To find out the size of a particular game, just download it after you have found it in the list and check the size of the PRG-ROM (FCEU and Nestopia can tell you that).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


